Reasoning: The paper discusses the development and calibration of a Monte Carlo compact model for oxide RRAM, which involves the use of electronic design automation (EDA) tools and simulation techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.ET (Electronic Design Automation) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the analysis of stochastic behaviors in cross-point RRAM arrays, which involves the use of statistical methods and simulation techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories, which are related to hardware design and optimization. Furthermore, the paper discusses the impact of interconnect wire resistance and array bias scheme on write functionality and energy consumption, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.EM (Electromagnetics) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) sub-categories, which are related to circuit analysis and simulation.
